@startuml
participant "User" as U
participant "GitHub Repository" as GH
participant "Use Case Catalog" as UC
participant "README.md" as RM
participant "Use Case README" as UCR
participant "Template" as T
participant "External Resources" as ER

U -> GH : Access repository
GH -> RM : Load README.md
RM -> U : Display repository overview
U -> UC : Browse use cases
UC -> UCR : Load specific use case
UCR -> U : Display problem statement and solution
U -> ER : Access linked AWS docs and courses
U -> T : Use template for contribution
T -> GH : Submit new use case
GH -> UC : Add new use case to catalog
@enduml